<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="Support page for visually impaired people with accessibility features.">
    <title>Support for Visually Impaired Individuals</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f8f8f8;
            color: #333;
            line-height: 1.6;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .pagg {
            text-align: center;
            color: #333;
        }

        h2 {
            color: #555;
        }

        .support-container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .support-container p {
            font-size: 1.1em;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        ul {
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .contact-info {
            background-color: #f1f1f1;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        .contact-info h3 {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .contact-info p {
            margin: 5px 0;
        }

        a {
            color: #1d72b8;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        /* Keyboard focus for accessibility */
        a:focus {
            outline: 2px dashed #000;
        }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #333;
            color: white;
            margin-top: 40px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <% layout("/layouts/boilerplate") %>


    <div class="support-container">
        <h1 class="pagg">Support for Visually Impaired Individuals</h1>
        <p>
            Welcome to our support page for visually impaired individuals. Here, you'll find information on tools, resources, and services to help you live independently and confidently. Whether you're looking for accessible technology, mobility solutions, or mental health support, we're here to assist.
        </p>

        <h2>Resources and Services</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Assistive Technology:</strong> Learn about screen readers, magnifiers, and other tools designed to help visually impaired individuals use computers, phones, and other devices.</li>
            <li><strong>Mobility Training:</strong> Access services that provide orientation and mobility training to improve your ability to navigate different environments safely.</li>
            <li><strong>Educational Support:</strong> Get connected to programs and resources that offer accessible learning materials, textbooks in Braille, and tutoring services.</li>
            <li><strong>Mental Health and Wellbeing:</strong> Access counseling services and community support networks that focus on emotional and psychological support for visually impaired individuals.</li>
            <li><strong>Employment Assistance:</strong> Find job placement services and vocational training opportunities tailored for people with visual impairments.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How We Can Help</h2>
        <p>
            Our team is dedicated to providing support and assistance to help you overcome challenges and achieve your goals. We can offer guidance on the best tools for your needs, connect you with local resources, and provide ongoing support. We work closely with organizations, schools, and healthcare professionals to ensure you receive comprehensive care and assistance.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact Us for Support</h2>
        <div class="contact-info">
            <h3>Contact Information:</h3>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@accessiblehelp.org">support@accessiblehelp.org</a></p>
            <p><strong>Phone:</strong> +1-800-123-4567</p>
            <p><strong>Address:</strong> 123 Accessible Lane, Tech City, 10001</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>How do I access screen reader software?</strong> – Most operating systems, such as Windows and Mac, have built-in screen readers. You can enable them through the accessibility settings on your device.</li>
            <li><strong>Are there grants available for assistive technology?</strong> – Yes, many non-profits and government programs offer grants to cover the cost of assistive devices. Contact our support team for help with applications.</li>
            <li><strong>What mobility aids are available for visually impaired individuals?</strong> – Tools like white canes, guide dogs, and electronic navigation aids can enhance mobility. Training services can help you choose the right aid for your needs.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    
</body>
</html>
